\c 2
\s1 Pengaturan tempat perkemahan bagi setiap suku
\p
\v 1 Lalu berfirmanlah TUHAN kepada saya dan Harun,
\v 2 “Setiap suku harus memasang tenda mereka masing-masing disekeliling Kemah Suci, namun tidak diperbolehkan mendirikan tenda-tenda itu terlalu dekat dan pembagian tempat perkemahan setiap suku ditandai dengan panji dan bendera lambang masing-masing suku.
\b
\p
\pi1
\pi1
\pi1
\pi1
\pi1
\pi1
\v 3-4 Tempat perkemahan Yehuda beserta suku-suku yang akan maju berperang bersamanya terletak di sisi/bagian timur, arah mata hari terbit, dan mereka akan mendirikan tenda mereka sesuai masing-masing divisi dan mengibarkan bendera mereka. Pemimpin keturunan Yehuda bernama Nahson, anak Aminadab, yang memimpin pasukan berjumlah tujuh puluh empat ribu enam ratus orang.
\pi1
\v 5-6 Suku Isakhar akan mendirikan perkemahan mereka di samping perkemahan suku Yehuda. Nama pemimpin mereka adalah Netaneel anak Zuar, dan jumlah pasukan dalam divisinya adalah lima puluh empat ribu empat ratus orang.
\pi1
\v 7-8 Kemudian pasukan suku Zebulon akan mendirikan perkemahan mereka disebelah/sisi suku Isakhar, dengan Helon sebagai pemimpin pasukan sebanyak lima puluh tujuh ribu empat ratus orang.
\pi1
\v 9 Jadi jumlah pasukan di sisi sebelah timur Kemah Suci sebanyak seratus delapan puluh enam ribu empat ratus orang. Ketiga suku ini yang memimpin bila bangsa Israel akan pindah ke lokasi lain.
\b
\pi1
\v 10-11 Suku Ruben, Simeon, dan Gad harus mendirikan tempat perkemahan mereka di sisi selatan Kemah Suci, dengan mengibarkan bendera suku mereka masing-masing. Elizur anak Syedeur yang memimpin empat puluh enam ribu lima ratus pasukan dari suku Ruben.
\pi1
\v 12-13 Di satu sisi perkemahan suku Ruben, suku Simeon harus mendirikan tempat perkemahan mereka. Selumiel anak Zurisyadai, yang memimpin pasukan Ruben sebanyak lima puluh sembilan tiga ratus orang
\pi1
\v 14-15 Eliasaf, the son of Deuel, will be the leader of the 45,650 men of the tribe of Gad.
\pi1
\v 16 So there will be 151,450 troops on the south side of the Sacred Tent. Those three tribes will follow the first group\add when the Israelis travel\add*.
\b
\pi1
\v 17 Behind that group will walk the descendants of Levi, who will carry the Sacred Tent. The Israelis will march in the same order that they always set up their tents. Each tribe will carry its own flag.
\b
\pi1
\v 18-19 The tribes of Ephraim, Manasseh, and Benjamin must set up their tents on the west side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and number of men whom they will lead:
\pi1 Elishama, the son of Ammihud, will be the leader of the 40,500 men of the tribe of Ephraim.
\pi1
\v 20-21 Gamaliel, the son of Pedahzur, will be the leader of the 32,200 men of the tribe of Manasseh.
\pi1
\v 22-23 Abidan, the son of Gideoni, will be the leader of the 35,400 men of the tribe of Benjamin.
\pi1
\v 24 So there will be 108,100 troops on the west side of the Sacred Tent. Those three tribes will follow the second group,\add behind the descendants of Levi\add*.
\b
\pi1
\v 25-26 The tribes of Dan, Asher, and Naphtali must set up their tents on the north side of the Sacred Tent, close to their tribal flags. These are the names of the leaders of those tribes and the number of men whom they will lead:
\pi1 Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai, will be the leader of the 62,700 men of the tribe of Dan.
\pi1
\v 27-28 Pagiel, the son of Ocran, will be the leader of the 41,500 men of the tribe of Asher.
\pi1
\v 29-30 Ahira, the son of Enan, will be the leader of the 53,400 men of the tribe of Naphtali.
\pi1
\v 31 So there will be 157,600 troops on the north side of the Sacred Tent. Those three tribes will be last. They must carry their own flags when the Israelis travel.”
\b
\pi1
\v 32 So there were 603,550 Israeli men who were able to fight who were listed according to their families' ancestors.
\v 33 But just as Yahweh had commanded, the names of the descendants of Levi were not included.
\b
\p
\v 34 The Israelis did everything that Yahweh had told Moses/me. They set up their tents close to their tribal flags, and whenthey traveled \add to a new location, they walked\add* with their own clans and family groups.